{
  "texts": [
    "To mitigate the noise introduced by retrieving documents for each subquery, we apply a pre-trained reranker that scores each candidate passage based on its relevance to the original complex query.",
    "This substantially improves precision by filtering out irrelevant results.",
    "In combination, question decomposition ensures broad evidence coverage, while reranking distills this expanded set into a concise collection of highly relevant passages.",
    "We evaluate our approach on the MultiHop-RAG and HotpotQA benchmarks and demonstrate substantial gains in recall and ranking metrics over standard RAG and single-component variants.",
    "We further analyze the inference overhead, showing that the added cost of QD remains manageable."
  ]
}